ze line 219 does invoke Class.forName(\\\"com.hazelcast.map.IMap\\\"), which throws a ClassNotFoundException.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting Hazelcast classes**\\n\\nI’m considering whether to use Hazelcast 3.12, which seems to be missing the class com.hazelcast.map.IMap, while the later versions do include it. I wonder if for line 219 in the same class initialization, the class1 of CLASS_NEAR_CACHE_STATS might still exist without IMap being available. I should check the 3.12 jar to confirm if it has com.hazelcast.nearcache.NearCacheStats and that there are no other relevant classes. Let's take a closer look.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_gtXaHdSIo4jTN0lWHur8pOy5|fc_0c7770d8cb7e365d016a41dbb33c1081959ca8003206850215", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "cd /tmp/hz && jar tf hazelcast-3.12.13.jar | grep -E 'com/hazelcast/(map/LocalMapStats|nearcache/NearCacheStats|map/IMap).class' || true\nfor v in 3.12.13 4.0 4.1 4.2.4 5.0; do echo ===$v; [ -f /tmp/hz/hazelcast-$v.jar ] || curl -sSLo /tmp/hz/hazelcast-$v.jar https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/com/hazelcast/hazelcast/$v/hazelcast-$v.jar; jar tf /tmp/hz/hazelcast-$v.jar | grep -E 'com/hazelcast/(map/LocalMapStats|monitor/LocalMapStats|nearcache/NearCacheStats|monitor/NearCacheStats|map/IMap|core/IMap).class'; done", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1626, "output": 1618, "cacheRead": 46080, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 49324, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782700955589, "responseId": "resp_0c7770d8cb7e365d016a41db9cac5c81958f2a79873cee98b8"}}
